    "Name": "Firefly",
    "Details": "Entering service in 2669, the Firefly was one of the standard light 'Mechs of the Star League Defense Force in its later years, with a small volume also entering service with all the Member State militaries. Although too slow when compared to other 'Mechs of similar weight to act as a scout, the Firefly instead served as a light support 'Mech, its superior armor and armaments allowing it to act as the anvil used by the rest of its lance to crush enemy scout forces. The 'Mech was also deployed independently in urban environments where its jump jets gave it a decisive edge against infantry and light combat vehicles and is useful in a guerrilla fighter role. This is a Clan variant of the Firefly that has been upgraded with all Clan technology and is also used by Wolf's Dragoons. The Firefly C is built on an endo steel chassis and is armed with four ER small lasers, three medium pulse lasers, and an SRM-2 launcher.",
